1
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:41,767
<i>I was able to say everything,
I wanted to say to Manuel.</i>

2
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:43,833
<i>I let out all of
my anger at Hazel.</i>

3
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:45,800
<i>I feel like I finally had
my closure.</i>

4
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:47,433
<i>Are you ready
zto forgive Manuel now?</i>

5
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:48,633
<i> Mom got hurt!</i>

6
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:50,367
<i>And you even want to meet with
your father?</i>

7
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:52,333
<i> I know that you're mad at him.</i>

8
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:54,600
<i>But do I have to feel hatred
towards him?</i>

9
00:00:54,733 --> 00:00:56,233
<i> But he has a new family now.</i>

10
00:00:56,367 --> 00:00:58,267
<i> Stop insisting on seeing him.</i>

11
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:00,200
<i>Your dad met with his mistress.</i>

12
00:01:00,333 --> 00:01:01,533
<i> You have a mistress?</i>

13
00:01:01,667 --> 00:01:04,367
<i>Mom, I can't believe dad has a
mistress.</i>

14
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:06,567
<i> Your dad lied to us.</i>

15
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:09,800
<i>He made me believe that
I'm the only woman in his life,</i>

16
00:01:09,967 --> 00:01:12,000
<i>We've become strangers
to each other.</i>

17
00:01:12,133 --> 00:01:14,100
<i>That's why I want you to get
to know me all over again.</i>

18
00:01:14,233 --> 00:01:15,400
<i> I want to pursue you.</i>

19
00:01:15,533 --> 00:01:17,500
<i>You have older siblings back
in the Philippines.</i>

20
00:01:17,633 --> 00:01:19,800
<i>Dad, do you still love
your first wife?</i>

21
00:01:19,933 --> 00:01:21,433
<i>Sweetie, I can't love her
anymore.</i>

22
00:01:23,267 --> 00:01:24,533
<i> I'm married to your mom now.</i>

23
00:01:30,933 --> 00:01:32,667
Mom, he's hurting Daisy.

24
00:01:34,033 --> 00:01:35,567
Daisy needs to get out of
that place.

25
00:01:36,833 --> 00:01:38,233
Before he hurts Tetay too.

26
00:01:39,133 --> 00:01:41,700
What kind of hold Lance have on
Daisy?

27
00:01:42,133 --> 00:01:44,000
Is it because he's her boss?

28
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:52,767
Or maybe he's threatening her
to fire her from her job.

29
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:54,733
You know what?

30
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:56,800
That's possible.

31
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:02,933
Or there could be a deeper
reason behind it.

32
00:02:04,067 --> 00:02:08,333
Or Daisy could be emotionally
dependent on him.

33
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,800
She might be scared of
losing him.

34
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,433
Whatever Daisy's
reason may be...

35
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:17,767
I won't allow Lance
to keep hurting her.

36
00:02:19,333 --> 00:02:21,933
Mom, I have to do something
to get her away from that jerk.

37
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:27,567
Noah and I will help you.

38
00:02:29,033 --> 00:02:32,200
We'll make sure that
Daisy will be safe,

39
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:33,867
especially Tetay.

40
00:02:34,933 --> 00:02:37,000
We will send out bodyguards.

41
00:02:39,667 --> 00:02:42,167
I won't let them hurt
my grandchild.

42
00:02:44,533 --> 00:02:46,000
That's why we have
to be careful.

43
00:02:48,867 --> 00:02:49,933
Rushing things...

44
00:02:50,533 --> 00:02:51,933
would push Daisy away.

45
00:02:55,033 --> 00:02:56,200
Talk to her.

46
00:02:56,933 --> 00:03:02,633
Let her know that you're just
concerned about their safety.

47
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:04,800
We'll go with you.

48
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:09,767
To make Daisy feel that
she's not alone.

49
00:03:18,633 --> 00:03:20,767
Yes, I'm on my way.

50
00:03:22,033 --> 00:03:23,233
Okay, bye.

51
00:03:26,467 --> 00:03:27,300
Oh!

52
00:03:27,567 --> 00:03:28,667
Good. You're here.

53
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:30,567
Huh? What happened?

54
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:32,133
I waited for you last night.

55
00:03:32,267 --> 00:03:33,467
Luckily, you found me
just in time.

56
00:03:37,533 --> 00:03:38,400
Oh?

57
00:03:39,533 --> 00:03:40,067
Why?

58
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:41,800
What's the matter?

59
00:03:42,667 --> 00:03:43,700
What's with the look?

60
00:03:44,733 --> 00:03:46,167
I know the truth, Mom.

61
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,700
About Dad's family
in the Philippines.

62
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:51,400
What you told me is a lie.

63
00:03:52,233 --> 00:03:53,500
Dad never had a mistress.

64
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:57,767
And you believe him?

65
00:03:58,033 --> 00:03:59,867
What are you even telling her?

66
00:04:00,467 --> 00:04:02,267
- It's all lies.
- Lies?

67
00:04:03,133 --> 00:04:04,800
How could Miss Felma be
Dad's mistress,

68
00:04:04,933 --> 00:04:07,233
if her children are way
older than me?

69
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:09,633
Dad didn't lie to me, Mom.

70
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:11,200
You did.

71
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:13,700
Why would you make up stories
just to turn me against Dad?

72
00:04:14,333 --> 00:04:15,467
He doesn't deserve this.

73
00:04:16,733 --> 00:04:18,100
What are you talking about?

74
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:20,233
You don't think I notice?

75
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:22,033
You treat him like crap.

76
00:04:22,167 --> 00:04:23,567
You control everything
in this house.

77
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:25,533
You don't let him get a job.

78
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,967
You keep him here like some
kind of unpaid housekeeper!

79
00:04:29,367 --> 00:04:32,533
Because I'm the one providing
for this family.

80
00:04:32,767 --> 00:04:34,267
I'm the one making money.

81
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:35,967
Right...

82
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:37,600
Because you're too busy at work,

83
00:04:37,733 --> 00:04:39,600
you're forgetting that
you're a mother too.

84
00:04:40,467 --> 00:04:42,767
Dad is the only one
who's always there for me.

85
00:04:44,133 --> 00:04:45,333
What am I hearing from you?

86
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:46,900
What is this about?

87
00:04:47,033 --> 00:04:49,033
So, you've been keeping
all that resentment

88
00:04:49,167 --> 00:04:50,600
against me, all this time?

89
00:04:50,933 --> 00:04:51,700
What?

90
00:04:52,233 --> 00:04:53,133
What's your problem?

91
00:04:54,467 --> 00:04:56,367
Suddenly, your dad's the hero?

92
00:04:57,467 --> 00:04:58,700
Let me remind you.

93
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:02,000
I'm the one feeding both of you!

94
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:06,233
I know that Mom, and I'm
grateful for that.

95
00:05:07,033 --> 00:05:09,867
But I need more than
just a roof over my head.

96
00:05:10,567 --> 00:05:11,833
You're my mother too.

97
00:05:12,667 --> 00:05:15,667
You're a nurse,
you take care of strangers.

98
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:17,900
But you couldn't even
take care of me.

99
00:05:18,033 --> 00:05:19,500
Jessica, that's enough.

100
00:05:19,633 --> 00:05:21,667
No Dad, she needs to hear it.

101
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:24,533
She was never there for me.

102
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:26,033
Unlike you.

103
00:05:26,167 --> 00:05:27,700
You made me feel loved.

104
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:29,967
You made me feel like
I mattered.

105
00:05:30,367 --> 00:05:32,533
And now, she wants me
to hate you?

106
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:35,633
Mom, you're so mean!

107
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,000
What now?

108
00:05:37,133 --> 00:05:38,700
- You've gone too far!
- That's enough!

109
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:39,900
Watch your mouth!

110
00:05:40,033 --> 00:05:41,167
Who do you think you are?

111
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:42,467
Why? You don't respect me
anymore?

112
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,900
Oh, What?

113
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:45,733
You two deserve each other!

114
00:06:04,433 --> 00:06:06,633
We're here now.

115
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,767
- Oh my, sweetie.
- I'm so excited.

116
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:10,933
Yes, I'm excited to see Tetay.

117
00:06:11,067 --> 00:06:12,700
- I will kill her!
- Let me go!

118
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:14,033
Have mercy on my daugter!

119
00:06:14,167 --> 00:06:16,067
- Let her go!
- What are you crying about?

120
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:17,667
Go ahead and bring out your man!

121
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,767
- I don't have anyone!
- I don't believe you!

122
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:21,600
- What's going on?
- You're making me a liar.

123
00:06:21,733 --> 00:06:24,933
Let me go!

124
00:06:26,667 --> 00:06:27,633
What?

125
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:31,267
Where's your guy at?
Get him out!

126
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,300
Get him out!

127
00:06:32,433 --> 00:06:35,333
- Please have mercy!
- Tetay, sweetie?

128
00:06:35,467 --> 00:06:36,533
Dad!

129
00:06:36,667 --> 00:06:37,633
Let her go!

130
00:06:39,567 --> 00:06:40,433
Get away!

131
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,733
Coward!

132
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:43,367
Don't hide behind the child!

133
00:06:43,633 --> 00:06:44,633
Is this your guy?

134
00:06:45,067 --> 00:06:46,567
Mom!

135
00:06:46,700 --> 00:06:47,700
Is he your man?

136
00:06:48,933 --> 00:06:49,833
Is it you?

137
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,433
What? Is it you?

138
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:58,600
Leave it be.

139
00:06:58,967 --> 00:07:00,000
We'll take care of him

140
00:07:04,267 --> 00:07:05,233
Jeff!

141
00:07:08,267 --> 00:07:09,933
- Uncle!
- Noah!

142
00:07:10,467 --> 00:07:11,467
Uncle!

143
00:07:12,033 --> 00:07:14,133
Uncle! Uncle!

144
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:16,733
Noah! Noah!

145
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:21,200
Noah! Noah!
Noah!

146
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:28,533
You beast!

147
00:07:30,333 --> 00:07:31,733
Help!

148
00:07:32,367 --> 00:07:33,433
Help!

149
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:37,933
Jeff, Help! Help!

150
00:07:38,067 --> 00:07:39,400
Let's bring him to the hospital!

151
00:07:39,533 --> 00:07:40,467
Let's help!

152
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:42,033
Uncle?

153
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:43,333
Jessica.

154
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,233
- Jessica...
- We're not done talking yet.

155
00:07:46,367 --> 00:07:47,967
- Don't talk back like that!
- That's enough!

156
00:07:48,133 --> 00:07:49,567
No! Why? Stay out of this!

157
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,367
You're enabling her, that's why
shes becoming rebellious!

158
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:52,533
You're ungrateful!

159
00:07:52,667 --> 00:07:53,700
Who are you so proud of?

160
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:54,933
Your dad?

161
00:07:55,067 --> 00:07:56,267
If you only knew!

162
00:07:56,667 --> 00:07:57,700
Of what?

163
00:07:59,933 --> 00:08:00,833
<i> You're pregnant?</i>

164
00:08:00,967 --> 00:08:02,933
<i>Friend, You will get
in trouble!</i>

165
00:08:03,067 --> 00:08:05,833
<i>You know that
premarital sex is a crime here!</i>

166
00:08:05,967 --> 00:08:07,967
<i>You're so lucky to have
Charles.</i>

167
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,000
<i> He loves you.</i>

168
00:08:09,133 --> 00:08:10,767
<i>You'll find someone
like him too.</i>

169
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,133
<i> I think I found someone,</i>

170
00:08:12,267 --> 00:08:15,400
<i>or more on getting someone
I can rely on to raise my baby.</i>

171
00:08:15,533 --> 00:08:16,967
<i> You were intoxicated.</i>

172
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:18,600
<i> You forcibly kissed me.</i>

173
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:19,933
<i> Oh my God, Friend.</i>

174
00:08:20,067 --> 00:08:21,967
<i>Is this the person you said
would help you with your baby?</i>

175
00:08:22,133 --> 00:08:24,300
<i>So you'll have Manuel carry
the responsibility?</i>

176
00:08:24,433 --> 00:08:26,567
<i>How are you going to convince
him that its his baby?</i>

177
00:08:26,967 --> 00:08:27,767
<i> It's easy.</i>

178
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:29,800
<i> I'll just wait a couple weeks.</i>

179
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:32,000
<i>I'm sure my pregnancy
won't be showing by then.</i>

180
00:08:32,133 --> 00:08:33,467
<i> He'll never know...</i>

181
00:08:34,167 --> 00:08:35,967
<i>that I'm pregnant for
two months now.</i>

182
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:37,467
Go on, Hazel, get in the room.

183
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,267
No! I need to discipline her!

184
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,467
Go on, Go on.

185
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,100
- No! I'm not done with her!
- I'll talk to her myself.

186
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:43,800
Stop it Manuel,
you're hurting me.

187
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:57,567
Sweetie, why did you talk

188
00:08:57,700 --> 00:08:58,733
to your mom like that?

189
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:03,067
I'm sorry, Dad.

190
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:07,600
I couldn't resist letting out
my frustrations at Mom.

191
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:10,967
I can't believe
she badmouthed you to me

192
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:12,700
and made me angry at you.

193
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:16,267
I understand, Sweetie,
but what you did was wrong.

194
00:09:17,267 --> 00:09:18,967
She's not right either, Dad.

195
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:22,933
You told me you made a huge
mistake with your family

196
00:09:23,067 --> 00:09:23,900
back in the Philippines.

197
00:09:24,667 --> 00:09:26,500
And it was because of Mom.

198
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:27,967
She's the bad guy.

199
00:09:28,733 --> 00:09:29,767
Jessica.

200
00:09:31,267 --> 00:09:32,700
Jessica, listen.

201
00:09:33,933 --> 00:09:38,033
Your mom is just trying
to protect you.

202
00:09:38,567 --> 00:09:39,767
She did that because
she's a mother.

203
00:09:41,033 --> 00:09:43,000
Yes, what she did
to me and Felma is wrong,

204
00:09:43,133 --> 00:09:44,567
and to my children.

205
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:48,267
But for your sake she only did
what's right.

206
00:09:49,233 --> 00:09:51,400
Because she wants you
to have a father.

207
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:55,033
How can you still defend her,
Dad?

208
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:58,900
Sweetie, I'm not trying to
defend her.

209
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:01,067
Whatever our problem is,

210
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,367
it's between me and her.

211
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,467
I just don't want you to see
your mom in a bad light.

212
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:09,333
No matter what happens,

213
00:10:09,467 --> 00:10:11,333
at the end of the day,
she's still your mom.

214
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:14,267
Aren't you mad at her?

215
00:10:15,233 --> 00:10:16,600
Because of her,

216
00:10:16,733 --> 00:10:18,700
you were forced
to leave your family before,

217
00:10:18,833 --> 00:10:21,667
and you didn't get a chance
to ask them for forgiveness.

218
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:26,133
Sweetie, I'll still get a
chance to ask them for
forgiveness.

219
00:10:26,267 --> 00:10:27,400
Now is not the time.

220
00:10:28,333 --> 00:10:29,133
Okay?

221
00:10:29,267 --> 00:10:30,433
Come on.

222
00:10:31,267 --> 00:10:33,967
Promise me, you'll apologize
to your mom later, okay?

223
00:10:35,233 --> 00:10:36,200
All right, that's enough.

224
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:37,400
Don't cry sweetie.

225
00:10:40,867 --> 00:10:42,067
Promise?

226
00:10:54,567 --> 00:10:56,967
Ma'am after were done here...

227
00:10:57,567 --> 00:11:00,800
we'll refer Tetay
to social welfare services,

228
00:11:01,267 --> 00:11:03,600
to get an assessment from a
psychologist.

229
00:11:03,733 --> 00:11:05,567
It's a standard protocol
to check,

230
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:08,567
if the child has
psychological trauma.

231
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:10,867
Sir Lance wouldn't let go of
me.

232
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:14,233
I'm glad my dad arrived.

233
00:11:14,933 --> 00:11:16,633
And then he let me go.

234
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:20,333
And then my mom hugged me...

235
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:24,333
Then she brought me
inside our house.

236
00:11:25,067 --> 00:11:29,733
And then, I don't know know
what happened next.

237
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,167
Tetay seem fine,

238
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:36,467
but we still need her checked
by a psychologist.

239
00:11:36,767 --> 00:11:38,267
It's protocol.

240
00:11:38,667 --> 00:11:39,633
Yes, Ma'am.

241
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:44,233
Thank you, Jeff.

242
00:11:45,533 --> 00:11:46,667
If...

243
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:49,867
you hadn't shown up, who knows
what would have happened.

244
00:11:52,533 --> 00:11:54,533
I will take care of you
from now on.

245
00:11:57,267 --> 00:11:59,100
Have you heard from
your Uncle Noah.

246
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:01,967
Yes, he's in surgery now.

247
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:03,933
I'm still waiting for update
from Mom.

248
00:12:04,733 --> 00:12:06,667
He got dragged into my
problems.

249
00:12:07,067 --> 00:12:09,033
I hope nothing bad happens
to him.

250
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,633
I know Uncle Noah,
he's a fighter.

251
00:12:13,267 --> 00:12:14,833
I'm sure, he'll get through
this.

252
00:12:15,467 --> 00:12:16,567
Don't worry.

253
00:12:18,633 --> 00:12:20,233
- Are you okay now?
- I'm okay.

254
00:12:44,633 --> 00:12:45,733
- Mom!
- Mom!

255
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:47,800
- Sweetie.
- Mom, here's your water.

256
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:49,233
Thank you.

257
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:57,567
- Oh, Nurse?
- Nurse, how is Noah doing?

258
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,233
Are they done with the surgery?

259
00:12:59,533 --> 00:13:02,400
Not yet, Dr. Cortes is still
doing the operation.

260
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:04,933
Ma'am excuse me,
I need to attend to an ER call.

261
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,633
My God.

262
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:38,067
You don't want to stay
at my house?

263
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:40,500
We are okay here, Jeff.

264
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:44,267
We're safe here now,
Lance is now detained.

265
00:13:45,033 --> 00:13:46,133
Remember what I told you?

266
00:13:46,267 --> 00:13:49,367
When I said I will pursue you
again.

267
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:52,033
Daisy, I'm serious
when I said that.

268
00:14:02,033 --> 00:14:03,767
I'm not ready yet, Jeff.

269
00:14:06,233 --> 00:14:08,267
I just got away,

270
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:11,467
from three years of toxic
relationship with Lance.

271
00:14:13,633 --> 00:14:15,133
You stayed with him for
three years?

272
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:19,167
Yes.

273
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:21,900
Yes, I can't leave him,

274
00:14:22,033 --> 00:14:24,400
because he threatened me that
he'll hurt Tetay if I do.

275
00:14:32,867 --> 00:14:33,933
I'm sorry, Daisy

276
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:40,500
I didn't get you away from
that beast quickly enough.

277
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:48,933
It's over now.

278
00:14:50,567 --> 00:14:54,067
But I have to admit...

279
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,633
When I got in relationship
with him...

280
00:14:58,800 --> 00:14:59,867
I was broken.

281
00:15:01,967 --> 00:15:03,667
He broke me.

282
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:09,667
This is my only chance
to pick up the pieces.

283
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:14,000
But don't worry.

284
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,367
I won't get in a way with
your relationship with Tetay.

285
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:20,567
Thank you.

286
00:15:21,833 --> 00:15:22,933
I'm content with that.

287
00:15:24,633 --> 00:15:25,600
For now...

288
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:28,933
I will wait,
I'll be right here.

289
00:15:31,867 --> 00:15:33,567
While you're still working
on yourself.

290
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,300
Daisy, I will wait for you.

291
00:15:38,967 --> 00:15:39,967
Just call me...

292
00:15:41,367 --> 00:15:42,867
whenever you need something,
okay?

293
00:15:46,067 --> 00:15:47,133
Okay.

294
00:16:09,133 --> 00:16:11,833
Sis, calm down, okay.

295
00:16:11,967 --> 00:16:13,467
Take a deep breath.

296
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:17,833
Noah's not going to die.

297
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:21,867
He still have a mission here
on earth.

298
00:16:23,467 --> 00:16:24,967
To get you to say yes.

299
00:16:28,267 --> 00:16:30,200
So please, sis.

300
00:16:31,233 --> 00:16:35,133
Once he recovered
you better say yes.

301
00:16:35,267 --> 00:16:36,300
Promise?

302
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:40,900
He's been a big part of
your life.

303
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:42,900
Your children's life.

304
00:16:43,767 --> 00:16:46,400
What else can you ask for?

305
00:16:46,533 --> 00:16:48,500
He's so kind.

306
00:16:52,033 --> 00:16:54,067
Handsome, rich.

307
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:56,033
What else do you need?

308
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:59,200
And the most exciting part...

309
00:16:59,867 --> 00:17:03,033
the best part,
he didn't just love you.

310
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:08,900
He loves your children too.

311
00:17:11,067 --> 00:17:15,800
You've seen how he risked
his life for Jeffrey, Right?

312
00:17:20,467 --> 00:17:21,967
- Excuse me.
- Doctor.

313
00:17:23,467 --> 00:17:25,100
The surgery is succesful.

314
00:17:25,233 --> 00:17:26,967
- Thank you.
- Fortunately,

315
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:28,800
the injury wasn't too severe.

316
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:29,900
He's stable now.

317
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,733
Thank God.

318
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:37,233
The next twenty four hour,

319
00:17:37,367 --> 00:17:38,600
to forty eight hours
will be crucial.

320
00:17:38,733 --> 00:17:42,300
We need to monitor him
for any signs of complication.

321
00:17:42,867 --> 00:17:44,600
But for now, he is safe.

322
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:50,467
Doctor, can we see him now?

323
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:53,267
Your husband is not fully awake
yet.

324
00:17:54,267 --> 00:17:56,833
But he'll be up,
maybe in an hour.

325
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:58,400
Excuse me.

326
00:17:58,533 --> 00:18:00,067
- Thank you, Doc.
- Thank you.

327
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,733
- Thank you, Doc.

328
00:18:04,067 --> 00:18:04,933
Mrs?

329
00:18:05,067 --> 00:18:06,433
Why are you laughing?

330
00:18:06,567 --> 00:18:07,967
No reason, Mrs!

331
00:18:10,933 --> 00:18:13,133
Silly! Knock it off, okay?

332
00:18:16,567 --> 00:18:18,733
So going back to the Philippines
has been a disaster!

333
00:18:19,367 --> 00:18:20,200
I really thought,

334
00:18:20,333 --> 00:18:21,800
your relationship with Manuel is
stronger.

335
00:18:23,533 --> 00:18:24,600
Well, that's what I thought too.

336
00:18:25,467 --> 00:18:29,700
But he's still not over that
sausage vendor!

337
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,433
I feel like a loser, Alice.

338
00:18:32,567 --> 00:18:33,333
Why?

339
00:18:34,033 --> 00:18:36,100
Because despite my efforts,

340
00:18:36,233 --> 00:18:38,133
Manuel still hasn't learn
to love me.

341
00:18:40,167 --> 00:18:42,633
And now Jessica is being
rebellious.

342
00:18:43,567 --> 00:18:44,900
She's siding with Manuel.

343
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:47,433
Why don't you just divorce him?

344
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:52,267
Like me and Charles, we're
happily divorced.

345
00:18:52,767 --> 00:18:53,400
No.

346
00:18:55,633 --> 00:18:59,633
Alice, I fell in love with
Manuel.

347
00:19:05,167 --> 00:19:05,833
And one more thing...

348
00:19:07,567 --> 00:19:09,700
I don't want to ruin my image.

349
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:12,900
My family think that
I have the most perfect life.

350
00:19:15,667 --> 00:19:17,367
So you really fell for him?

351
00:19:18,433 --> 00:19:20,167
I already told you before,
remember?

352
00:19:21,467 --> 00:19:23,300
It's not hard to love Manuel.

353
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,800
Yes...

354
00:19:27,933 --> 00:19:29,400
You just said it yourself.

355
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:33,100
But Manuel is not totally
into you.

356
00:19:34,067 --> 00:19:37,700
Especially now that
he'd seen Felma again.

357
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:42,867
For sure their feelings for
each other got rekindled.

358
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:45,600
I need to be vigilant.

359
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:51,100
I need to watch his every move.

360
00:20:13,467 --> 00:20:15,167
<i>- Are you drunk?
- It's none of your business!</i>

361
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:20,233
<i> You jerk!</i>

362
00:20:20,367 --> 00:20:22,400
<i> Get out of your car!</i>

363
00:20:22,667 --> 00:20:23,500
<i> What are you doing?</i>

364
00:20:23,633 --> 00:20:24,867
<i>You're having
an attitude with me,</i>

365
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,400
<i> after you almost run me over?</i>

366
00:20:28,533 --> 00:20:31,033
<i>Instead of apologizing,
you chose to argue with me!</i>

367
00:20:31,167 --> 00:20:32,433
<i> Why do I have to apologize?</i>

368
00:20:32,567 --> 00:20:35,733
<i>You know what, if you can't be
responsible on the road,</i>

369
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:39,033
<i>can you not wander around when
you're drunk?</i>

370
00:20:39,167 --> 00:20:40,267
<i> I'm not drunk.</i>

371
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:45,233
<i>My family's going through
a lot right now.</i>

372
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,700
<i>That's why we ended up
like this.</i>

373
00:20:47,833 --> 00:20:50,433
<i> That's not a reason to steal!</i>

374
00:20:50,567 --> 00:20:52,367
<i> Can you let it go this time?</i>

375
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:53,800
<i>He's asking you for forgiveness.</i>

376
00:20:53,933 --> 00:20:54,967
<i> And who are you?</i>

377
00:20:55,733 --> 00:20:56,800
<i> I'm their friend.</i>

378
00:21:00,267 --> 00:21:05,233
<i> Happy birthday to you...</i>

379
00:21:05,367 --> 00:21:06,667
<i> Oh, blow, blow, blow...</i>

380
00:21:12,300 --> 00:21:13,800
<i> Thank you so much, Noah.</i>

381
00:21:17,133 --> 00:21:17,833
<i> Jeff!</i>

382
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:23,600
Thank you, Noah.

383
00:21:24,933 --> 00:21:27,200
You're the reason
why I'm able to get back up.

384
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:31,133
When Manuel abandoned me,

385
00:21:33,833 --> 00:21:35,067
Not ever...

386
00:21:36,667 --> 00:21:38,133
you never left my side.

387
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:43,033
Sorry.

388
00:21:43,967 --> 00:21:47,533
Sorry, if I wasn't able to repay
all the kindness you showed me.

389
00:21:49,067 --> 00:21:53,467
Sorry if you feel like I
couldn't accept...

390
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,433
your love.

391
00:21:56,800 --> 00:21:57,967
The truth is...

392
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:08,967
Noah!

393
00:22:09,100 --> 00:22:10,067
I'm sorry!

394
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:12,033
I'm sorry, I'm sorry!

395
00:22:12,167 --> 00:22:14,400
I'm so happy that
you're awake now!

396
00:22:16,233 --> 00:22:17,133
I'm sorry.

397
00:22:17,267 --> 00:22:19,633
Wait, did I touch your wound?

398
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:21,033
What?

399
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:23,767
So...

400
00:22:24,900 --> 00:22:26,067
What's the truth?

401
00:22:30,533 --> 00:22:31,500
I've heard you.

402
00:22:34,733 --> 00:22:35,567
You said...

403
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:41,800
Sorry, if I feel like you
couldn't accept my love.

404
00:22:45,367 --> 00:22:46,667
So, what's the truth?

405
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:51,567
Do you love me too, Felma?

406
00:23:11,567 --> 00:23:14,033
Do you love me too, Felma?

407
00:23:36,967 --> 00:23:38,167
Hey, Jeffrey!

408
00:23:38,300 --> 00:23:40,733
You brought flowers!

409
00:23:40,867 --> 00:23:42,500
Is that for Daisy?

410
00:23:43,700 --> 00:23:46,667
No. Daisy asked me
to stop by Dangwa.

411
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:48,900
So, I bought flowers for
Uncle Noah.

412
00:23:49,033 --> 00:23:49,967
She wants to thank him.

413
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:51,033
Actually, me too,
we want to thank him.

414
00:23:51,167 --> 00:23:53,633
So, that's from Daisy and
Jeffrey.

415
00:23:53,767 --> 00:23:55,733
That's so sweet!

416
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:57,800
Daisy...

417
00:23:59,233 --> 00:24:00,267
Are you back together?

418
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:01,400
No!

419
00:24:02,133 --> 00:24:03,067
Not yet.

420
00:24:04,467 --> 00:24:05,733
She said, there's still

421
00:24:05,867 --> 00:24:06,833
some issue in her life,
she needs to fix.

422
00:24:06,967 --> 00:24:08,967
But she won't stop me from
seeing Tetay.

423
00:24:09,467 --> 00:24:12,000
- Oh!
- So there's still hope...

424
00:24:12,767 --> 00:24:15,400
I think once
she got her life together,

425
00:24:15,533 --> 00:24:16,700
I just need a little push...

426
00:24:16,833 --> 00:24:18,200
and our family will be together.

427
00:24:18,333 --> 00:24:22,767
What's that, what's that?
They'll be together.

428
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:24,000
You're both overeacting.
Let's go.

429
00:24:24,133 --> 00:24:25,667
- Who's overeacting?
- Sorry, we're rooting for

430
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:26,933
your love team!

431
00:24:29,467 --> 00:24:31,000
Come on!

432
00:24:37,133 --> 00:24:38,900
You really do love me Felma.

433
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:43,400
I have feelings for you for
awhile now.

434
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:49,400
At first I'm not sure if it's
gratitude...

435
00:24:50,833 --> 00:24:52,700
or because we're friends.

436
00:24:53,867 --> 00:24:56,567
But when you almost died,

437
00:24:57,633 --> 00:25:01,200
I realized that I can't live
without you.

438
00:25:02,767 --> 00:25:06,767
Not because of gratitude,
or because of friendship.

439
00:25:07,900 --> 00:25:09,100
Because I love you.

440
00:25:10,533 --> 00:25:12,633
That's the best kind of love,
Felma.

441
00:25:13,767 --> 00:25:16,000
No explanation needed.

442
00:25:16,433 --> 00:25:18,000
I feel the same.

443
00:25:21,733 --> 00:25:22,967
I love you, Felma.

444
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:25,867
No explaination.

445
00:25:27,467 --> 00:25:29,100
No condition.

446
00:25:41,567 --> 00:25:43,800
The kids...

447
00:25:44,133 --> 00:25:45,867
She said yes, already!

448
00:25:46,333 --> 00:25:47,600
We're together now!

449
00:25:48,133 --> 00:25:49,367
- There!
- Oh my!

450
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:52,667
- Congratulations, Uncle Noah!

451
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:54,867
Sorry, sorry!

452
00:26:01,667 --> 00:26:04,933
- Congrats!
- Thank you!

453
00:26:15,533 --> 00:26:17,267
Why did you burn it?

454
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:19,667
This is the only memories
I have left of them.

455
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:21,200
Because that's
the right thing to do!

456
00:26:21,333 --> 00:26:23,733
You're so hard to love!

457
00:26:23,867 --> 00:26:26,367
You know what?
We should part ways!

458
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:27,933
You're not posting that,
are you?

459
00:26:28,067 --> 00:26:29,333
Oh yes, I am.

460
00:26:29,633 --> 00:26:32,067
I want the whole world
what kind of woman Felma is!

461
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:35,533
Let's not wait any longer,
we're not getting any younger.

462
00:26:35,933 --> 00:26:38,033
Wait, did you asked
the children for permission?

463
00:26:38,167 --> 00:26:39,700
- We're okay with it! We
approve!

464
00:26:39,933 --> 00:26:40,700
- Sis!

465
00:26:40,833 --> 00:26:41,600
Open the website!
Open it! Come on!

466
00:26:41,733 --> 00:26:42,767
- Our website! Open it!
- What website?

467
00:26:42,933 --> 00:26:44,567
Our website! Open it!

468
00:26:44,833 --> 00:26:46,367
<i>- I'm not a mistress!
- Oh really?</i>

469
00:26:46,500 --> 00:26:48,733
<i>You're a mistress!
Mistress! Look at her!</i>

470
00:26:48,867 --> 00:26:49,800
<i> She's a mistress!</i>

471
00:26:49,933 --> 00:26:50,967
<i> Look! The mistress!</i>
